==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hypoxanthin
<hw>Hy`po*xan"thin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>hypo-</ets> + <ets>xanthin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A crystalline, nitrogenous substance, closely related
to xanthin and uric acid, widely distributed through the animal body,
but especially in muscle tissue; -- called also
<altname>sarcin</altname>, <altname>sarkin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypozoic</ent>⟦br⟧
